```

For preprocessing I extract pixel values in a very easy way and "convert and copy" them to my 1d float representation of the image.
```
private static float[] VerySlowBitmapTo1dFloatArrayConverter(Bitmap image)
{
    List<float> floatImage = new List<float>();

    for (int row = 0; row < image.Height; ++row)
    {
        for (int column = 0; column < image.Width; ++column)
        {
             var pixelValues = image.GetPixel(column, row);
             floatImage.Add(pixelValues.R / 255.0f);
             floatImage.Add(pixelValues.G / 255.0f);
             floatImage.Add(pixelValues.B / 255.0f);
        }
    }

    return floatImage.ToArray();
 }
```

